<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-702-487  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 702 487.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE on andamp; about ATandamp;T  Dec 17, 1990 v5 n125 p23(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Semiconductor industry: industry growth forecast in 1991. (surveyfor Semiconductor Equipment and Materials International conductedby Dataquest)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Dataquest Inc. (Surveys).andO;Topic:     Semiconductor IndustryPreview of Coming YearGrowthSalesSurveySemiconductor Equipment and Materials InternationalIndustry Analysis.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Electronic equipment companies, semiconductor manufacturers and theirequipment and materials suppliers predict an upturn in sales next year,according to an industry survey released Wednesday.andM;The survey was conducted for Semiconductor Equipment and MaterialsInternational (SEMI) by Dataquest.andP;  It showed that North American electronicequipment companies expect sales to be up 5 percent in 1991, compared with a3 percent rise this year.andP;  Those companies also predict that their purchasesof semiconductor devices will rise by 12 percent in 1991, compared with 2percent this year.andM;Worldwide, semiconductor manufacturers, which recorded sales growth of 2percent in 1990, forecast sales to jump 11 percent next year.andM;Semiconductor equipment companies predict an average sales increase of 17percent in 1991.andP;  Materials suppliers forecast a 10 percent increase.andO;Equipment companies reported that Asia/Pacific market and Japan will continueto be their primary markets in 1991.andM;SEMI is an international trade association serving the $20 billionsemiconductor equipment and materials industry.andP;  Headquartered in MountainView, SEMI has regional offices in Brussels, Seoul, Tokyo and Washington.andO;</TEXT></DOC>